<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1174] Logging Admin Servlet broken for multicore, cannot submit form</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1174</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-554&quot; title=&quot;Hierarchical JDK log level selector for SOLR Admin&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-554&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-554&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the original improvement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has a bug in it.  If I submit the form using multicore, it goes to /solr/admin/logging (not the right path).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing this is because of the path trickery in SolrDispathFilter but I can&apos;t follow what the best procedure is to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The simplest thing to do is to not use request.getRequestURI() because a form with no action submits to itself.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
